I'm in need of some self-improvement/purification. this will be a 3 week challenge: Tuesday March 14th until the morning of Tuesday April 4th. The guidelines are as follows:

10 minutes of meditation every day
Eat MINIMAL preservatives, MAXIMAL organics
No make-up wearing during the daytime
No more than 30mins of television per day
15 minutes of stretching every day
At least 40 minutes of exercise per day (when well enough to do so). 
Singing and/or dancing in room to music of choice (played loudly of course)
NO EATING PASTRIES AT WORK
Read Emily Dickenson every day

Mom: "Hey jean, what is 'freaking'? Is that a kind of dance style? I saw an article i the newspaper on it."

hiked like hella to get to this internet cafe! i emailed a very select group of friends, so sorry to everyone who didnt get one. im staying in a village that is seriously more rural than most of you have ever imagined. me and my partner kayla are teaching classes to 45 little honduran kids, 4 days a week. all in spanish. thaaats right, bitches. its amazing here. too bad the food is terrible. but today we hiked into another town to go to this marketplace that happens twice a month. bought soo much fruit for wayyy less than a dollar. oh yes. anywho, this is way to crazy to explain in one little lj entry, so ill just stop trying. basically my summer is awesome, and all you idiots are doing is sitting around, getting drunk and getting fat! 

sincerely suck it,
jean
